Class IdentitySimplifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.udel.cis.vsl.sarl.simplify.common.IdentitySimplifier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Transform<SymbolicExpression,SymbolicExpression>, UnaryOperator<SymbolicExpression>, Simplifier

    public class IdentitySimplifier
extends java.lang.Object
implements Simplifier
    A trivial implementation of Simplifier which does nothing: given an expression, it returns the expression unchanged.

      • assumptionAsInterval

        public Interval assumptionAsInterval(SymbolicConstant symbolicConstant)
        Description copied from interface: Simplifier
        If the assumption can be represented as a simple interval constraint, i.e., an expression of the form A <= x <= B, where A and B are concrete numbers, x is the given symbolic constant, and <= could be < in either case, this returns the interval [A,B] (or (A,B], or, ...). Else returns null.

      • substitutionMap

        public java.util.Map<SymbolicConstant,SymbolicExpression> substitutionMap()
        Description copied from interface: Simplifier
        In the process of simplifying the initial context, this simplifier may have "solved" for some of the symbolic constants occurring in the context. This method returns a map in which the keys are those symbolic constants and the value associated to a key is the "solved" value. The solved value will be substituted for the symbolic constants in any expression given to the Transform.apply(S) method of this simplifier.
        Specified by:
        substitutionMap in interface Simplifier
        Returns:
        a mapping from some symbolic constants occurring in original context to their solved values

      • getReducedContext

        public BooleanExpression getReducedContext()
        Description copied from interface: Simplifier
        Returns the reduced context associated to this Reasoner. This expression may differ from the original one used to create the Reasoner because it was simplified or put into a canonical form. Moreover, symbolic constants which have been "solved" may be removed from the context. (For the context with addtional equations giving those solved values, use method Simplifier.getFullContext()). This context will not change after creation.
        Specified by:
        getReducedContext in interface Simplifier
        Returns:
        the reduced context associated to this Reasoner

      • getFullContext

        public BooleanExpression getFullContext()
        Description copied from interface: Simplifier

        Returns the full context associated to this Reasoner. This expression may differ from the original one used to create the Reasoner because it was simplified or put into a canonical form. The full context includes equations where one side is a symbolic constant and the other is the solved value. (For the context without those equations, use method Simplifier.getReducedContext()). Hence the expression returned is equivalent to the original given expression.

        This context will not change after creation.

        Specified by:
        getFullContext in interface Simplifier
        Returns:
        the reduced context associated to this Reasoner
